    "### 8. Correlation Heatmap (All Relationships)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "corr = bd.correlations(method='pearson')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\"\"\n",
    "CORRELATION HEATMAP:\n",
    "\n",
    "COLOR MEANINGS:\n",
    "  🔴 RED    = Positive correlation (both increase together)\n",
    "  🔵 BLUE   = Negative correlation (opposite changes)\n",
    "  ⚪ WHITE  = No correlation (no relationship)\n",
    "\n",
    "CORRELATION VALUES:\n",
    "  +1.0  = Perfect positive (always increase together)\n",
    "  +0.7  = Strong positive\n",
    "  +0.3  = Moderate positive\n",
    "   0.0  = No relationship\n",
    "  -0.3  = Moderate negative\n",
    "  -0.7  = Strong negative\n",
    "  -1.0  = Perfect negative (always opposite)\n",
    "\n",
    "FORMULA (Pearson):\n",
    "  r = Σ((x - μₓ)(y - μᵧ)) / √(Σ(x - μₓ)² × Σ(y - μᵧ)²)\n",
    "\n",
    "⚠️ IMPORTANT:\n",
    "  Correlation ≠ Causation!\n",
    "  Just because variables are related doesn't mean one causes the other\n",
    "\"\"\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 9. Outlier Detection"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "outliers = bd.outliers(method='iqr')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\"\"\n",
    "OUTLIER DETECTION (IQR METHOD):\n",
    "\n",
    "FORMULA:\n",
    "  IQR = Q3 - Q1\n",
    "  Lower Bound = Q1 - 1.5 × IQR\n",
    "  Upper Bound = Q3 + 1.5 × IQR\n",
    "  → Values outside bounds = OUTLIERS (shown as red dots)\n",
    "\n",
    "WHY 1.5 × IQR?\n",
    "  ✓ Statistical standard in box plot analysis\n",
    "  ✓ Approximately 0.7% of normal data flagged as outliers\n",
    "  ✓ Good balance between sensitivity and specificity\n",
    "\n",
    "INTERPRETATION:\n",
    "  ✓ Few outliers (< 5%) = Normal data\n",
    "  ✓ Many outliers (> 10%) = Unusual data or errors\n",
    "  ✓ Check outliers: Real or data entry errors?\n",
    "\"\"\")"
   ]
  },
